# Cross-domain — Skill Combination

This rule complements backend.md and frontend.md. Applies when the task crosses domains —
not triggered by file but by task context.

## New feature (endpoint + component + store + tests)

Core: [SKILL_BACKEND] + [SKILL_FRONTEND]
Conditional: [SKILL_STATE] (if touches store), `typescript-advanced-types` (if complex types)
Testing: `vitest` + `javascript-testing-patterns` + [SKILL_BACKEND] (HTTP tests)

## Auth flow (tokens + middleware + login)

Core: [SKILL_BACKEND] + [SKILL_FRONTEND]
Consult: `docs/security.md` completely before modifying

## Theming (if applicable)

`color-palette` generates shades + CSS tokens that [SKILL_COMPONENT_LIB] consumes as
anatomy and token reference. When creating a new theme, activate both: first `color-palette`
to generate, then [SKILL_COMPONENT_LIB] to integrate into the component system.

## `session-close`

Exclusive: only explicit verbal trigger from the user. Not combined with work flows.
